00:17:15.359 --> 00:17:20.730
So we use the method
of spectroscopy

00:17:20.730 --> 00:17:25.819
to explore the outer
atmosphere of the star.

00:17:25.819 --> 00:17:30.075
And with that we can bridge
very large distances.

00:17:30.075 --> 00:17:31.450
And it's almost
like we're taking

00:17:31.450 --> 00:17:34.650
a little piece of
the star and looking

00:17:34.650 --> 00:17:37.970
